Class Wind

  • java.lang.Object
    • danaus.Wind
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Wind>

    public class Wind
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Wind>
    An instance represents one unit of wind, which has a non-negative intensity and a cardinal direction.

    • Method Detail

      • parseWind

        public static Wind parseWind(java.lang.String s)
        Parse s into a wind object and return the object. Precondition: s has one of the following forms: 30 N, N 30, 30N, N30. where 30 can be replaced by any nonnegative integer and N can be replaced by any of the directions N, NE, E, SE, S, SW, W, NW. Throw a WindFormatException if s is not well-formed.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Wind w)
        Return a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer depending on whether this object is less than, equal to, or greater than obj.

        Comparisons are made first on the direction's row change, then on the direction's column change, and then on the intensity.
